radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal atelectasis in bilateral lung bases posteriorly, several scattered millimetric hypodensities in the liver suggestive of cysts or biliary hamartomas, normal pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands, 1.6 cm cyst in the mid right kidney, a predominately hypoattenuating 3.5 cm lobulated mass adjacent to the greater curvature of the stomach, enlarged appendix with a maximum diameter of 9 mm and a possible obstructing appendicolith.
